# Afric – Static Website Testing

This project showcases my QA testing work on the **Afric** static website. The primary focus was to verify website content, UI consistency, responsiveness, and the successful implementation of requested changes.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

* **Project Name:** Afric
* **Project Type:** Static Website
* **Testing Type:** Manual Testing
* **Focus Area:** Content Verification, UI Testing & Functional Validation

---

## 🧪 Testing Scope

During this project, I performed testing on the following areas:

* Website content verification
* Text and image updates
* Navigation and page links
* UI consistency across pages
* Responsive layout verification
* Cross-browser functionality
* Blog page verification after implementation

---

## 🐞 QA Activities

* Verified all requested content changes
* Checked newly added blog page functionality
* Validated page layouts and responsiveness
* Identified and reported UI or functional issues when necessary
* Performed final regression testing before project approval

---

## 🛠 Tools Used

* Manual Testing
* Google Chrome DevTools
* Cross-Browser Testing

---

## 🧠 Key Learnings

* Testing and validating static websites after content updates
* Ensuring UI consistency across different pages and screen sizes
* Performing regression testing after implementing new features
* Improving attention to detail during final QA verification

---

## 🚀 Conclusion

This project strengthened my practical experience in testing static websites, verifying content updates, and ensuring that all requested changes were implemented correctly before deployment.

